quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  29,39,"팇We팈 also 팇destroyed팈 Korah, Pharaoh, and Ham칙n. Indeed, Moses had come to them with clear proofs, but they behaved arrogantly in the land. Yet they could not escape 팇Us팈"
  29,40,"So We seized each 팇people팈 for their sin: against some of them We sent a storm of stones, some were overtaken by a 팇mighty팈 blast, some We caused the earth to swallow, and some We drowned. Allah would not have wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  29,41,"The parable of those who take protectors other than Allah is that of a spider spinning a shelter. And the flimsiest of all shelters is certainly that of a spider, if only they knew"
  29,42,"Allah surely knows that whatever 팇gods팈 they invoke besides Him are 팇simply팈 nothing. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  29,43,"These are the parables We set forth for humanity, but none will understand them except the people of knowledge"
  29,44,Allah created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Surely in this is a sign for the people of faith
  29,45,"Recite what has been revealed to you of the Book and establish prayer. Indeed, 팇genuine팈 prayer should deter 팇one팈 from indecency and wickedness. The remembrance of Allah is 팇an팈 even greater 팇deterrent팈. And Allah 팇fully팈 knows what you 팇all팈 do"